cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper deals with the phenomenon of profile name reuse on Twitter, which involves the dynamics of user accounts and their behavior. This topic is related to several sub-categories of computer science, including social networks (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), multimedia (cs.MM), and security and privacy (cs.CR). However, given the focus on analyzing large-scale data and characterizing the accounts involved, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (social and information networks).
